<br>
Actually I would say that most of these classes deal with agro differently.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Shadow Knights</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Gain Agro: Taunt, Lifetaps, DOTs, Nukes, Snare, +Agro Buffs<br>
Shadow Knights pretty much rule everyone with gaining agro, and they also have the most options agro gaining options. They outright suck with shedding unwanted agro.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Paladins</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Gain Agro: Taunt, Stun, Heals, Root<br>
Drop Agro: Root<br>
Paladins have solid agro gaining abilities as mobs react well to stuns and even attempts to being stunned. Even their heal spells can be used to gain agro by healing that person who is outagroing them thus transfering the agro. Their only real method for dumping unwanted agro is to root and back off. While this works in many situations, it will not work on mobs which are immune to run spead changes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bards</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Gain Agro: DOTs, Slow<br>
Drop Agro: Escape<br>
Other: Mezmerize, Charm, Invulerability<br>
Bards are more limited in their agro gaining abilities, and often times the group needs to work with the bard to ensure he keeps it. If they need to shed unwanted agro quickly, they can use Escape [which I think is an AA skill.] They also have songs to mezmerize and charm mobs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Rangers:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Gain Agro: Taunt, Snare, Nukes, DOTs, Root<br>
Drop Agro: Jolt, Root<br>
Rangers are very flexable due to being very good at both gaining and dropping agro. Both our bows [requiring one to step away from the mob] and more limited tanking abilities keep us from running around trying to tank everything in sight.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Warriors</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Gain Agro: Taunt, AE Taunt<br>
Warriors clearly need some help here. The fact that they get Enraging Blow weapons makes this even more apparrent that a warrior on his own does not have everything he needs to deal with agro. They seem almost the opposite of rangers in this regard being more limited in dealing with agro, but having high tanking ability in return.<br>
<br>
