<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7584">Dinian Scalebane</a></b><br>
<i><span style="font-size:11px">Overlord of <a href="http://www.endorean.com/">Endorean</a></span></i></span></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hyardgune>Hyardgune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/03 3:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1832.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: heh</span><hr size=1> details, details.  Crydee's main point remains valid and it's the same point many of us have brought up, all we have is taunt and gear.<br>
<br>
It's like I've said before, even with all the armor and hit point gear to make a warrior into Norrath's biggest pinata, the only difference between us and a pinata is that the pinata gets hit.<br>
<br>
It's not hard to outaggro a warrior and many times the people who are outaggroing us are folks doing essential parts of their job in a group (chanters, clerics especially).  Those casters have no incentive to group with a melee-type that can't reliably keep aggro when they can get sometime who they know can.<br>
<br>
We aren't talking about Sebilis anymore, in the days when if you lost aggro, the chanter would take a few hundred points of damage even if taunt failed once.  Back then, yeah aggro was an annoyance and knights did it better, but the difference was marginal.  Guess what?  Times have changed and we're the dinosaurs, defined by a 3 expansion old ability and slowly on the road to becoming the 5th choice for xp groups.<br>
<br>
I'm a good tank, I know my job, I do it well, but my gear isn't good and I'll never see an EB weapon, so instead, I'm leveling a SK because I don't want to have to scrape my friends off the ground after every other pull. <p>Ghune<br>
10 Ogre Shadowknight<br>
